channel.title: Need help [Portforwarding]
channel.description:
hey guys i've been portforwarding for a while and i used to be able to get my servers up, but then once i got a new router [XFINITY] Router my server hasnt been working when i go on ( www.canyouseeme.org ) it can see my port but when i put no-ip into my Loaders.java and i compile i get a js5connect and on the progran (DUC 3.0) it shows a Ip (ROUTER/NAT) that is no where close to mine, is the ip (ROUTER/NAT) suppose to be the same as your default gateway ip. i'm getting really confused and i have no idea what to do i've spent over a week trying to figure this out!
Questions ~~~~~~~ is there anyway i can get people to connect to my server by just putting my ipv4 ip instead of the no-ip?

item.title: Need help [Portforwarding]

item.description:
@xx_matty_xx wrote:

maybe your router doesn’t support upnp, or has it disabled? if that’s what you’re using to do the portforwarding…
